    <introduction>
        <p>In the last section, we focused on solving systems of equations by graphing. In addition to being time consuming, it can be difficult determine the exact solution when it contains fractions. There are two algebraic methods for solving systems of linear equations, and in this section we will use the <term>substitution method</term>.</p>
        <figure>
            <caption>Alternative Video Lesson</caption>
            <video youtube="HxhacvH49o8"/>
        </figure>
    </introduction>

    <subsection>
        <title>Solving Systems of Equations Using the Substitution Method</title>

    <!--Insert article from 
http://www.joeydevilla.com/2014/12/31/the-new-york-times-unintentionally-provided-the-answer-to-their-question-is-algebra-necessary/
